    <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
    <tr>
        <td id="descriptionArea">
            <p>Companies have a lot of documents regarding their process, projects or individual drug development works. To provide an interface, a new document management page will be added.</p>

<p> </p>

<p>A document can be top-level or project-specific. In main page, document management link will appear in left panel. Through main page, document management platform will show documents by project or with no filter.</p>

<p> </p>

<p>In project mode(when workflow appears in left panel), there will be a document management link in left panel again. Through project workflow, document management page will show only documents that are under selected project.</p>

<p> </p>

<p>RAG system will consume these documents during chat. When a project is selected, it will consume documents that are connected to that project and documents that are top-level (no projects). It will be informed if the document is connected to the project or not.</p>

<p> </p>

<p>When a project is not selected, RAG system will include all documents from all projects and top-level (no project) documents.</p>

<p> </p>

<p>Components:</p>
<ul>
	<li>Document management Page: Includes "Upload Document" button which shows document upload panel on click. Also, existing documents table, filterable by document fields.</li>
	<li>Document Upload Panel: Includes fields: File, Title, Category, Project</li>
	<li>Document Table: Showing existing documents (filter by title, category, project)</li>
</ul>


<p> </p>

<p>Tests:</p>

<p> </p>

<p>User's can upload new documents to the platform.</p>

<p>User's can see and filter existing documents.</p>

<p>When project is not selected, users can see all documents in the platform.</p>

<p>When project is selected, users can see only the documents in the project.</p>

<p>When project is not selected, RAG system includes all documents in the platform.</p>

<p>When project is selected, RAG system only includes documents that are connected to the project and the documents with no projects.</p>
            <br/>
        </td>
    </tr>
